dcterms:description: The EyePACS dataset contains high-resolution labeled images of human retinas exhibiting varying degrees of diabetic retinopathy. It consists of 35,126 training, 10,906 validation, and 42,670 test images, each graded by a medical expert on a scale from 0 (no diabetic retinopathy) to 4 (proliferative diabetic retinopathy).
dcterms:title: EyePACS Dataset

dcterms:description: The APTOS 2019 Blindness Detection dataset contains labeled images of human retinas exhibiting varying degrees of diabetic retinopathy, collected in India from a different patient population. It includes 80% of the images (2,929 images) as a test set and 20% (733 images) as a secondary validation set, with images being noisier and containing distinct visual artifacts.
dcterms:title: APTOS Dataset
